sebio Castigliano]] \n*34.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Pietro Ferraris]]  \n*35.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Guglielmo Gabetto]] \n*35.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Giuseppe Grezar]] \n*30.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Ezio Loik]]  \n*33.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Virgilio Maroso]]  \n*17.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Danilo Martelli]]  \n*38.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Valentino Mazzola]]  \n*14.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Romeo Menti]]  \n*29.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Franco Ossola]]  \n*13.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Dante Piani]]  \n*34.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Mario Rigamonti]]  \n*13.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Francesco Rosetta]] \n*3.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Guido Tieghi]]  \n\n====Goalscorers====\n*29.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Valentino Mazzola]] \n*19.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Guglielmo Gabetto]] \n*13.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Franco Ossola]] \n*12.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Ezio Loik]] \n*8.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Eusebio Castigliano]] \n*8.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Pietro Ferraris]]  \n*4.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Giuseppe Grezar]]  \n*1.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Danilo Martelli]]  \n*6.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Romeo Menti]]  \n*2.{{flagicon|ITA}}[[Guido Tieghi]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n* {{cite book|author=Fabrizio Melegari (a cura di).|title= ''Almanacco illustrato del calcio - La storia 1898-2004'', Modena, |publisher=Panini, 2004.}}\n* {{cite book|author=Fabrizio Melegari e Luigi La Rocca|title=Storia del Campionato Italiano dal 1942-43 al 1949-50|chapter=Calciatori 1942-43|publisher=edizione speciale per \"La Gazzetta dello Sport\" Franco Cosimo Panini Editore, Modena, 2005}}\n==See also==\n[[Grande Torino]]\n\n{{Torino F.C.}}\n{{Torino F.C. seasons}}\n{{1946\u201347 in Italian football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1946-47 Torino F.C. season}}\n[[Category:Torino F.C. seasons]]\n[[Category:Italian football clubs 1946\u201347 season|Torino]]\n[[Category:Scudetto-winning seasons]]\n\n{{Italy-sport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|{{more footnotes|date=April 2020}}{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}}}\n\n{{Infobox football club season\n|club = [[Torino F.C.|Associazione Calcio Torino]]\n|season = 1946-47\n|manager = [[Luigi Ferrero]]<ref>{{Worldfootball.net|luigi-ferrero}}</ref>\n|chairman = [[Ferruccio Novo]]\n|stadium=[[Stadio Filadelfia]]\n|league = [[Serie A]]\n|league result = [[1946-47 Serie A|1\u00ba]] \n|league topscorer = [[Valentino Mazzola|Mazzola]] (29)\n\n|pattern_b1 = _collar\n|pattern_so1 = _black_band_color\n|leftarm1 = 831d1c\n|body1 = 831d1c\n|rightarm1 = 831d1c\n|shorts1 = FFFFFF\n|socks1 = 831d1c\n\n|pattern_b2 = _collar\n|pattern_so2 = _black_band_color\n|leftarm2 = FFFFFF\n|body2 = FFFFFF\n|rightarm2 = FFFFFF\n|shorts2 = 831d1c\n|socks2 = 831d1c\n|prevseason = [[1945\u201346 A.C. Torino season|1945\u201346]]\n|nextseason = [[1947\u201348 A.C. Torino season|1947\u201348]]\n}}\nDuring the'''1946-1947''' [[Torino F.C.|Associazione Calcio Torino]] competed in Serie A.\n==Summary==\nAfter winning the championship last season, the team clinched again the title with a great performance in the second part of the season with a format of sole group. [[Valentino Mazzola]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enciclopediadelcalcio.it/Mazzola.html|title=Mazzola, Valentino|publisher=Enciclopedia Del Calcio|language=Italian|accessdate=25 February 2017}}</ref> scored a massive 29 goals to help Torino reached a back-to-back championship.\n\nThe wounds of war were healing and football returned to a single-round system<ref>{{cite web|title=''Tre squadre soltanto retrocederanno dalla A alla B''|publisher=Corriere dello Sport|date= 22 August 1946 |url=http://dlib.coninet.it/bookreader.php?&c=1&f=5495&p=3#page/2/mode/1up}}</ref>. The league, due to the immediate difficulties to find the sixteen best teams, was played with a huge tournament of twenty teams, then occupying 38 days, from September to July 1947. Torino did not make substantial changes to its team, but had strengthened the park of players. Along with the return of Romeo Menti<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.figc.it/it/nazionali/nazionali-in-cifre/dettaglio-convocato/?calciatoreId=45180&squadraId=12|title=Menti, Romeo|publisher=figc.it}}</ref>, came the midfielder Danilo Martelli from Brescia<ref>R. Ossola-F. Tavella, ''\"Il romanzo del Grande Torino\"'', Newton & Compton, Roma, 1993, pp. 203-204</ref>\n, the back-stopper Francesco Rosetta of Novara<ref name=\"figc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.figc.it/it/nazionali/nazionali-in-cifre/dettaglio-convocato/?calciatoreId=45401&squadraId=12|title=Rosetta, Francesco|publisher=FIGC|language=Italian}}</ref>, the goalkeeper Dante Piani, the Vercellese Guido Tieghi.\n\nFrom the 21st round the Granata returned to the lead<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dlib.coninet.it/bookreader.php?&c=1&f=6875&p=1#page/1/mode/1up|date=29 July 1947|title=Grande Torino 1947|publisher=Corriere dello Sport}}</ref>, gradually strengthening their position and subsequently winning the tournament, with a ten-point lead over Juventus. Torino, after a last misstep with Sampdoria (the only team in the tournament to take away three points out of four from Torino) put together a sixteen match unbeaten run, of which fourteen were victories, beginning with the derby won by Guglielmo Gabetto<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enciclopediadelcalcio.it/Gabetto.html|title=Gabetto, Guglielmo|publisher=Enciclopedia del Calcio|language=Italian|accessdate=30 May 2015}}</ref>, to go to other successes such as the five goals against Inter and Atalanta, the six against Vicenza, Genoa and Milan. That attack ended with 104 goals scored, an average of nearly three per game, and with Valentino Mazzola Serie A top-scorer.\n\n== Squad ==\nSource:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://calcio-seriea.net/rose/1946/253/|publisher=calcio-seriea.net|title=Rosa toro 46|language=Italian}}</ref>\n{{fs start}}\n{{fs player|pos=GK|nat=ITA|name=[[Valerio Bacigalupo]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=GK|nat=ITA|name=[[Dante Piani]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=DF|nat=ITA|name=[[Aldo Ballarin]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=DF|nat=ITA|name=[[Virgilio Maroso]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=DF|nat=ITA|name=[[Mario Rigamonti]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=DF|nat=ITA|name=[[Francesco Rosetta]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=MF|nat=ITA|name=[[Eusebio Castigliano]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=MF|nat=ITA|name=[[Giuseppe Grezar]]}}\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|pos=MF|nat=ITA|name=[[Ezio Loik]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=MF|nat=ITA|name=[[Danilo Martelli]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Pietro Ferraris]] II}}\n{{fs player|pos=FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Guglielmo Gabetto]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Valentino Mazzola]]}} (Captain)\n{{fs player|pos=FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Romeo Menti]] II}}\n{{fs player|pos=FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Franco Ossola]]}}\n{{fs player|pos=FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Guido Tieghi]]}}\n{{fs end}}\n\n=== Transfers ===\n<div style=\"float: left; width: 50%;\">\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;width:99%;\"\n\n! colspan=\"4\" | In\n|-\n! width=3% | Pos.\n! width=32% | Name\n! width=30% | from\n! width=35% | Type\n|-\n| GK || [[Dante Piani]] || Triestina}} || \n|-\n| DF || [[Francesco Rosetta]] || Novara}} || \n|-\n| MF || [[Danilo Martelli]] || [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]] ||  (5.200.000 \u00a3)\n|-\n| FW || [[Romeo Menti|Romeo Menti II]] || [[Fiorentina]] || ''loan ended''\n|-\n| FW || [[Guido Tieghi]] || [[Pro Vercelli]] || \n|}\n</div>\n<div style=\"float: left; width: 50%;\">\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;width:99%;\"\n\n! colspan=\"4\" | Out\n|-\n! width=3% | Pos.\n! width=32% | Name\n! width=30% | To\n! width=35% | Type\n|-\n| GK || [[Alfredo Bodoira]] || Alessandria}} || \n|-\n| DF || [[Sergio Piacentini]] || [[Sampdoria]] || \n|-\n| MF || [[Alfonso Santagiuliana]] || [[Vicenza Calcio|Vicenza]] || \n|-\n| FW || [[Oreste Guaraldo]] || Novara || ''loan out''\n|-\n| FW || [[Adriano Zecca]] || Modena || \n|}\n</div>\n{{clear}}\n\n== Competitions ==\n=== Serie A ===\n{{main|1946-47 Serie A}}\n====League table====\n{{:1946-47 Serie A|showteam=TOR}}\n==== Matches ====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 22 September 1946\n|time = 15:30 [[UTC+1]]\n|round = 1\n|team1 = Torino\n|team2 = Triestina\n|score = 1-1\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1946/3709/